# Chapter 18: Handwritten Digit Recognition using CNN and PyTorch

## Project Overview

This project implements a Handwritten Digit Recognition Web Application using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) trained on the MNIST dataset.

The application predicts handwritten digits in real time and demonstrates the practical use of Deep Learning for image classification.

---

# Problem Statement

Computers cannot naturally understand handwritten characters.

The objective is to train a CNN model capable of recognizing handwritten digits accurately.

---

# Dataset Information

Dataset: MNIST

Training Images: 60,000

Testing Images: 10,000

Classes: 10

Digits: 0–9

Image Size: 28 × 28 Pixels

